	"metadata": {
		"title": "CVE-2017-8797 kernel: NFSv4 server does not properly validate layout type when processing NFSv4 pNFS LAYOUTGET operand (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2017-8797",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2017-8797",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: It was found that the NFSv4 server in the Linux kernel did not properly validate layout type when processing NFSv4 pNFS LAYOUTGET and GETDEVICEINFO operands. A remote attacker could use this flaw to soft-lockup the system and thus cause denial of service. \n            STATEMENT: This issue does not affect the versions of the Linux kernel as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5, 6 as the code with the flaw is not present in the products listed.\n\nThis issue affects the versions of the Linux kernel as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7 and Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2. Future kernel updates for these products may address this issue.",
